        <div id="purpose">
            <h4 class="mb-0">Purpose & Founding</h4> <hr class="nogap" />
            <p>
                I, Eli Bell, founded Thin Blue Lie on 6/05/2020 at the beginning of the George Flloyd/Breonna Taylor
                protests. I was 17 year olds at the time and had no previous programming experience. Naively, I thought
                that I could design, build, and release a database and website in a couple of months; it took nearly 6.
                I'm growing up mixed race in an overwhelmingly white neighboorhood showed me just how different people
                can react to police misconduct. I founded Thin Blue Lie to prove just how massive an issue this is.
                Thin Blue Lie exists to educate, and to channel the anger so often seen online, towards charities
                and towards actual action.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div id="howitworks">
            <h4 class="mb-0">How Thin Blue Lie Works</h4> <hr class="nogap" />
            <p>
               Taking after Stack Exchange, Thin Blue Lie implements a <a href="/About/Reputation">Reputation system</a> where the more you
               contribute to the website, the more privledges and power you get. We also have a pretty lenient set of 
               <a href="/About/Rules">Rules</a>. 
            </p>
        </div>
        <div id="future">
            <h4 class="mb-0">Roadmap</h4> <hr class="nogap" />
            <p>
                Thin Blue Lie currently only has one contributor, it's founder Eli Bell. Because he just started
                learning how to program, it's taking a while for things to get done. In the future, however, we are
                hoping to flesh out the website much more, provide more essays, solution, and resources.
                <a class="d-block" href="/About/Roadmap">Read more</a>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div id="contributors">
            <h4 class="mb-0">Thanks</h4> <hr class="nogap" />
